cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the need for better support for clinicians and analysts working with healthcare data, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper proposes a structural framework for explicit domain knowledge, which involves the use of linked data, a topic that falls under the categories of databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in visual analytics and the applicability of the proposed framework in a specific domain, physiotherapy, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
